
	<div class="post">
		<h1 class="title">Hash Digest Generator</h1>
		<div class="entry">

			<p>Type in any string up to 50 characters long into the box and hit hash.<br>
			This will generate md5, sha1 and sha256 digests for that string.</p>

			<form action="/hash" method="post">

				<input type="text" name="hashstring" size="50" maxsize="50"> <input type="submit" value="Hash">
			</form>

				<br><br>

				<dl>
					<dt>MD5</dt> <dd>{{hash.md5}}</dd>
					<dt>SHA1</dt> <dd>{{hash.sha1}}</dd>
					<dt>SHA256</dt> <dd>{{hash.sha256}}</dd>
				</dl>

				
				<br><br>
				<p><small>Note: I do not save these values but... Don't try to hash your passwords online anywhere.</small></p>
		</div>
	
	</div>

